Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Coat #oven-ready tray{} with @nonstick cooking spray{}. Gently separate @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%ounce}.

In #oven-ready tray{}, combine @marinara sauce{2.5%ounce}, @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Add ravioli; stir until evenly coated.

> For 4 servings, divide everything evenly between two trays.

Evenly top ravioli mixture with @spinach{5%ounce}. TIP: Spread the spinach out and press down, making sure no leaves hang over the edges of your tray!

Coat a large piece of #foil{} with nonstick cooking spray. Cover tray tightly with prepared foil. Bake on middle rack until ravioli are tender and spinach has wilted, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> For 4, bake two trays side by side on middle rack.

When ravioli bake is almost done, halve and toast @ciabatta bread{1} until golden brown. Immediately spread with @butter{1%tbsp}; halve ciabatta on a diagonal.

> For 4 servings, use 2 tbsp butter.

Remove foil from spinach ricotta ravioli bake (careful—watch out for steam!). Stir to thoroughly combine spinach. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide between shallow bowls; top with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve with toasts on the side.